Jul 23 2009 	I loved this place!!!	We decided to take a trip to Vegas but wanted to see a few other places besides the Strip. We came across The Resort on Mount Charleston online and decided to make it our home base. It was wonderful to come here every night after a full day because it was always so much cooler. We stayed here the 2nd week of July when temps in Vegas were over 100. It is only about 45 minutes from the Strip and yet, because it's a little way up the Mountain, the evening temps are so cool that you might want to wear a sweater while sitting on the patio. The room was nice and clean and the bathroom had been redone recently. There was a small fridge, coffeemaker, hair dryer, ironing board and iron. The AC was a little difficult to figure out and we never did figure out how to turn it off. Also a Big Screen TV. Not many channels but we're not really big TV watchers. I can't comment on the food because we always ate elsewhere and returned in time to grab a drink at the bar. The bar closes up at 9:30 pm during the week and is open later on the weekend. For me, the best part is the pond out front. It's filled with large colorful fish and a family of ducks. Duck food can be had for a small price and children enjoyed feeding the momma duck and her babies. I loved sitting on the patio with the fountain and the wildlife, reading for a few minutes and relaxing. Everyone was very friendly, especially the bartender. The guy knew what I wanted every night after the first night. Nice place.	
