Feb 19 2005	Majestic Wonderland!	My husband and I have lived in Las Vegas for more than a year, but we'dnever been to Mt. Charleston or the Mt. Charleston Hotel. We'd heard that the hotel was being refurbished under new ownership, and that seeing the improvements was definitely worth a drive up the mountain. What better day than Valentine's Day to check it out!The entire experience was awesome! The scenic hotel is beautifully nestled among snow-covered mountains and fragrant fir trees. The fresh air couldn't have been more crisp and clean. Whether inside or outside, this piece of paradise could make anyone feel rejuvenated!The moment we stepped into the architecturally unique dining room for the Valentine's Day brunch, we were treated like royalty. The staff was warm and friendly, the live music was perfect and the food was incredible! From the first sip of mimosa to the last bite of cheesecake, the total presentation was first class! Our Valentine's Day at the Mt. Charleston Hotel was an event we'll treasure forever. Even if you're from another planet, don't miss this majestic wonderland!	
Feb 15 2005	Disappointed...	My husband and I planned to stay at the hotel for the night before Valentine's Day for a romantic getaway. We were excited but skeptical because of the reviews we'd read. We should have listened. Upon entryt to our (non-smoking) room, we found cigarette burns on the chair, and on the blanket. The shower and bathroom had dirty/black grout resembling mold. Not to forget, the toilet seat had urine stains on the seat. There was no evidence of room service, restaurant information, or other basics in a hotel room. The overall feel of the room was dirty and deary, but we overcompenstated by humoring the situation. The dinner in the hotel's restaurant could have had a better selection. (Only 5 things to choose from, cheapest being $17/plate.) We had terrible service by a waitress whom had worked the lunch shift in the bar, and by her shirt - you could tell. It was supposed to be the romantic, quiet dinner for two that turned into choking down a high fat expensive steak and waiting 15 minutes for a response from anyone for dessert, a check, anything!! We did, however, had a great time earlier in the day up at the Mt. Charleston LODGE (near the cabins) and returned there for dessert because we had such a horrible time at the hotel. We would have headed home, but at that point we probably had too much to drink. When we checked out in the morning, I had to go over our bill wondering why a mysterious extra $30 was tacked on. Oh, it turned out to be a holding fee for the room. We never cancelled, and we showed up, so why would be charged a fee afterward? It got cleared up with ease as a simple mistake. I was really surprised by our experience there. We thought it would be a better situation and more guest friendly. So, beware: Don't go with too many expectations! Advice? Book a cabin further up the road! Although more money, its worth it!	
