Aug 19 2004	Buyer beware	I had heard good things about Mt. Charleston so my wife and I thought it may be a nice place to get married. The idea of being married there was the only thing that went smoothly. When we check-in and went to our rooms we were appalled, the rooms were dark and dirty. There was no way I was going to stay the night in such a place or have my out-of town relatives stay there. We went right back to the office to ask for a refund. The staff was very rude and accusatory towards us when we asked for a refund. It took serveral hours of talking to them before they gave our wedding party a refund for one of the two days we had reserved. We had to eat the money on one of the nights. All I can tell people thinking about staying at this hotel is beware, and expect slow, rude service and dirty rooms. We went ahead and got married there but was very unsatisfied with the level of service we received and the cleanliness of the place.	
