Dec 31 2003	Filthy way outdated they call it 'rustic'.	Stayed 1 night 12/30/03. Hotel desk staff was not rude, but not pleasant either. Very matter of fact. &quot;no this, no that&quot;. We had 2 double beds on the first floor. Very outdated. Probably done in the 70's. Bathroom and room was filthy. The room has no centralized heater- it has 1 small space heater bolted on the wall with a filter. The room has 2 chairs/no table. Bathroom is tiled w/ grout so filthy it looked black! TV works, no Fox channel though. Guests that night seemed to be families w/ small children, yet the hotel is not kid friendly at all. It has a dining area w/ views of the canyon- this is probably what's keeping this hotel going. I doubt if there are any returning guests there... You're better off getting a hotel in the Summerlin area, a few exits off I-95... Don't go to this hotel. You will be wasting your $$. We got up at 7am the next day and dashed out of there....	
Mar 6 2003	Brief Visit	We were only able to enjoy the restaurant the night we visited. The scene could have been from a romance novel. It was lightly snowing, which only enhanced the view from the panoramic windows. The food was above average, but the service was a little slow. The fireplaces added even more to the evening. We were able to see the suite on the second floor. It was average, but the picture on their web-site is of the 3rd floor suite and it seems to be very nice with its vaulted ceilings. All the personnel were very nice and helpful. There is no elevator so be prepared for a haul if you bring lots of luggage. We do plan stay there next year in the 3rd floor suite. The lodge at the top of the mountain is cheaper and supposedly has Jacuzzi tubs, but they seemed snobbish and wouldn't let us see a cabin.	
